Key Match Events: Fotis Ioannidis scored two goals for Greece at the 23rd and 76th minutes.
Benjamin Kallman scored an own goal for Finland at the 37th minute.
Matti Peltola (Finland) was shown a yellow card for a bad foul in the 90+3 minute.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Greece won the match 3-0 against Finland.
The match was held at Georgios Karaiskakis Stadium in Piraeus, Greece with an attendance of 17,293.
